{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1784374222,"nonce":"rbxvc3M9S6MlXTVQuCrUtBP4mIQ=","message":"Phase 3 — PR 2 of the object series: PostgreSQL enums. MERGED PR #112 (squash 75ac61c). Epic stays OPEN.\n\nRetires the `Raw` fallthrough (postgresql/introspect.rs `sql_type` catch-all): a PG enum column now\nresolves to a modeled `CREATE TYPE … AS ENUM` (new `SqlType::Enum(String)` + `EnumModel { name, labels }`\non `SchemaModel.enums`) instead of referencing a type squealy never emits. Full VIEW-template thread:\nIR → diff/plan (Create/Drop/AlterEnum + risk) → KDL package → PG render (CREATE TYPE before dependent\ntables, schema-qualified column refs) + introspection (catalog identity via pg_type.typtype='e' / pg_enum)\n→ MySQL/SQLite reject → SchemaCapabilities.enums → CLI. MySQL inline ENUM/SET already round-trips (no work).\n\nScope decisions (maintainer):\n- SqlType::Enum(name) VARIANT (not keep-Raw), + FULL alter: additive `ALTER TYPE … ADD VALUE` (detected as\n  an ordered-subsequence label change → Safe); destructive relabel (remove/reorder) DEFERRED — rejected\n  loudly at render, a documented follow-up.\n- The SAME-NAME relation↔enum SWAP is REJECTED, not ordered. PostgreSQL auto-creates a composite type per\n  relation, so an enum can never share a table/view name. A topological planner (view graph + FK graph +\n  dependent-object severing) to order the swap was built across codex rounds 3-6 and proved UNBOUNDED\n  (dependent table → dependent view → FK → kept-repointed view → diamond topology), so on round 7 the\n  maintainer chose to reject the collision with a clear \"split the migration\" error instead. Guards:\n  `reject_enum_relation_name_collision` (model pair, in plan_models/check_create) +\n  `reject_enum_relation_collision_in_diff` (precomputed diff, in plan_diff → new PlanError).\n\ncodex rounds 8-11 (all real correctness edges, each pinned by a disable-to-fail test): create-path AND\nincremental-path enum-declaration validation over table + view columns (shared validate_enum_references);\ndrop/restore a column default around ANY type change (PG rejects an un-castable default during ALTER … TYPE\n— generalized from enum-only after round 11 found the enum-away and cross-schema-Raw directions); reject\nenum cast targets on MySQL/SQLite (they silently degraded to CHAR/TEXT). codex round 12 CLEAN.\n\nVerified: full workspace suite (60 binaries) + compile_fail + fmt + clippy -D warnings; live PG publish 7/7 +\nintegration 25/25, model publish 7/7, MySQL publish 13/13 + integration 2/2, SQLite in-process. CI test + MSRV green.\n\nNEXT = PR 3 (PG sequences): CREATE SEQUENCE / pg_sequence, taking care not to emit a standalone sequence for\none implicitly owned by an identity/serial column.","files":null}]}